[15:49:07] [DEBUG] [conductor] Codex worker sentinel-security event: {"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_43","type":"mcp_tool_call","server":"coordinator","tool":"post_update","arguments":{"type":"broadcast","content":"SECURITY FINDING: HIGH\nTask: task-007\nFile: worktracker/supabase/migrations/20240101000003_create_time_entries.sql\nLine: 18-19 (same pattern also in 20240101000004_create_active_timers.sql:18-19, 20240101000005_create_monthly_goals.sql:26-27, and insert policies in 20240101000006_rls_policies.sql:102-104, 141-143, 179-181)\nIssue: Cross-tenant category references are allowed because category ownership is never verified.\nDetail: `time_entries`, `active_timers`, and `monthly_goals` accept any existing `categories.id` as `category_id`, but the only auth check on insert/update is `auth.uid() = user_id` for the child row. A user who learns another tenant's category UUID can create rows that reference that foreign category, breaking tenant isolation and causing cross-tenant side effects when the victim deletes the category (`ON DELETE SET NULL` / `CASCADE`).\nRecommendation: Enforce same-owner references either with composite foreign keys like `(category_id, user_id) REFERENCES categories(id, user_id)` or with `WITH CHECK` / trigger validation such as `category_id IS NULL OR EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM public.categories c WHERE c.id = category_id AND c.user_id = auth.uid())` on every insert/update path, including RPC functions."},"result":null,"error":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
